\section{PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE}
\vspace{2pt}
{\sl Och Ziff Capital Management} \hfill New York, NY \\
Quantitative Analyst \hfill   April 2007 to January 2009  
   \begin{itemize} \itemsep -2pt % reduce space between items
   \item Designed and developed a Perl framework to carry out trading scenarios and simulations
   \item Analyzed performance of various hedges to determine if fund performance could be improved
   \item Tested a variety of factor regressions to try to explain fund performance in terms of the market
   \item Carried out various Principal Component Analyses to try to explain market conditions
   \item Created a system to detect market and data anomalies as well as an automated way to fix these issues
 \end{itemize}

{\sl ZS Associates} \hfill New York, NY \\
Associate \hfill July 2005 to April 2007
 \begin{itemize} \itemsep -2pt
  \item  Used Excel and VBA to model the impact that adding more sales reps would have on physician prescribing behavior in order to determine optimal sales force size
  \item Developed an Excel VBA tool to analyze the promotion system of a top five pharmaceutical company
  \item Created a physician segmentation using SAS and Excel that was used to focus and refine client targeting efforts
  \item Analyzed and reported on the goal setting process of a client and shared these findings with internal teams
  \item Managed a team that developed a tool to compare and summarize data from two different data vendors that would be fed into the client’s incentive compensation system
  \item Supported the incentive compensation system of over 10,000 sales representatives for a top five pharmaceutical company and facilitated the transition to a team in India
\end{itemize} \vspace{-6pt}

{\sl Cornell University} \hfill Ithaca, NY \\
Academic Technology Center Consultant \hfill June 2004 to May 2005
 \begin{itemize} \itemsep -2pt
  \item Encouraged professors to integrate technology into the classroom in order to improve teaching and learning effectiveness
  \item Aided professors in augmenting their courses with technology such as PowerPoint, Dreamweaver, and Photoshop
  \item Mentored new employees in the use of relevant software packages and tools
\end{itemize} \vspace{-6pt}

{\sl Prebon Yamane} \hfill Jersey City, NJ \\
Junior Programmer \hfill Summer 2001, 2002
 \begin{itemize} \itemsep -2pt
